      <Value><![CDATA[<p><span class="lead">Principal Duties</span></p>
<p>The duties and responsibilities listed below are intended to describe the general nature of the role. The balance between the elements of the role may change or vary over time depending on the specific needs at a specific point in time, or due to changing needs within the division/school.</p>
<p><strong> </strong><strong>General </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>To carry out the duties of the post in accordance with university policies and procedures;</li>
<li>To be aware of our Student Experience Strategy and to collaborate with our students as members of a community of learning in order to engender a student-centred learning experience;</li>
<li>To maintain a safe work environment, including ensuring compliance with legislation and the undertaking of risk assessments as necessary;</li>
<li>To contribute fully, and where appropriate lead, the administrative processes and committee structures of the Division, School, and university;</li>
<li>To work collaboratively and collegiately with colleagues and managers to deliver divisional and school objectives and make a leading contribution to the development of the broader academic and cultural direction of the university;</li>
<li>To provide academic leadership to their team, Division and the School, mentoring peers and colleagues and ensuring that teams work effectively together;</li>
<li>To lead on the development of appropriate dialogues and relationships with the subject community (academic, governmental and commercial) and its audiences, nationally and internationally;</li>
<li>To take a leading role in developing the external profile of the School, Division, Research Centre and programmes;</li>
<li>To maintain own continuing professional development and scholarship, responding flexibly to the changing demands of both the university and the subject field;</li>
<li>To undertake any other duties which may be commensurate within the role and grade as requested by the Head of Division and/or Dean of School.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Teaching and Learning</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>To undertake teaching and assessment at both PG and UG level, including: setting, marking and assessing coursework and examinations and provide appropriate feedback to students in line with university procedures;</li>
<li>Take a leading role in ensuring that the curriculum is relevant, current and meeting the needs of both students and employers, promoting the use of research-led teaching where appropriate;</li>
<li>To regularly collect, and respond to, student feedback;</li>
<li>Contribute to the supervision of undergraduate and postgraduate dissertations;</li>
<li>Identify opportunities for strategic development and contribute to the development of such opportunities, taking the lead where appropriate;</li>
<li>Take a leading role in the process of curriculum development, course modification, continuous and enhanced monitoring procedures and reviews by the university;</li>
<li>Actively contribute to the development and delivery of the teaching and learning strategy within the School and Division;</li>
<li>Utilise and support others to adopt innovative approaches to teaching and learning which includes research-led teaching;</li>
<li>To act as a personal academic tutor;</li>
<li>To undertake administrative roles relevant to the management and delivery of programmes, up to and including programme leadership;</li>
<li>Work with colleagues across the division and university to support course promotion, student recruitment and retention;</li>
<li>To be involved in doctoral supervision as appropriate;</li>
<li>Undertake other teaching-related administrative duties as appropriate.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Research, Knowledge Exchange and Impact</strong><strong> </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Pursue excellence in innovative and independent research, inspiring and supporting others to do the same;</li>
<li>Take a leading role in supporting the HoD and Dean to develop and deliver the research and innovation strategy within the School and Division, including REF submissions or equivalent;</li>
<li>Take a leading role in creating a positive research culture within the division/school;</li>
<li>To promote the integration of own research area with other research interests within and, as appropriate, outside the Division, School, and University;</li>
<li>To develop and maintain a regular output of high quality, internationally significant research publications in peer reviewed journals or other appropriate outlets;</li>
<li>To lead, support, and mentor other colleagues in the development of their research activities;</li>
<li>To initiate, lead, and collaborate in research initiatives with colleagues both within the Division/School/University and externally;</li>
<li>To develop and maintain a network of externally connections that support the development of research, knowledge exchange and innovation activities;</li>
<li>To proactively seek out, apply for, and secure significant research income;</li>
<li>To support and mentor others to seek out, apply for, and secure research income;</li>
<li>To lead on the development of knowledge exchange, innovation, and impact opportunities within the Division/School;</li>
</ul>]]></Value>
