    <introduction>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p><span class="lead">Role Purpose</span></p>
<p>The primary purpose of this role is to take a leading role in developing and enhancing the research, innovation, knowledge exchange, impact, and income generation activities within the division of Business, Enterprise, and Management, supporting delivery of the University strategy. To do so, the role holder will need to work collaboratively with an established team of academics, research centres, and relevant industry partners. The role holder will also be required to contribute fully to the delivery of undergraduate, postgraduate, and doctoral programmes, by teaching, assessing, and supporting students. They should be passionate about the student experience and committed to a research-led teaching approach. With the specialist knowledge required to teach across a range of undergraduate and postgraduate management modules, they will also have wider knowledge and expertise related to one or more of the following: Business Analytics, Digital Marketing and e-Business, Organisational Strategy, and Logistics and Supply Chain Management. As part of the role, they will also be required to liaise and support colleagues at our transnational partners who deliver Business Management degrees.</p>]]></Value>
    </introduction>
